      "content": "but its not just \"glitches\" tho. it's too precise. it's like everything related to my work in fintech and my old posts about privacy is what's being scrubbed. support just gives me these canned responses and says \"we have no record of data loss.\" it feels way more intentional than a sync error. like they're trying to make it so I don't exist online. is there any precedent for a company actually wiping a user's footprint like that?",
