      "content": "the \"rare\" thing is a bit dismissive i think. i've been reading about how big tech firms use \"shadow bans\" and \"content de-indexing\" for politics, but this feels different. this isn't just hiding my posts, it's the actual files and identity history. if a corp decides a person is a liability, why wouldn't they have the tools to basically erase them from the digital record to protect their reputation? it seems like a logical endgame if they wanted someone to disappear.",
